to celebrate the birthday of Ed Roberts with Doodle. Ed Roberts was one of the most influential Disability Rights activists in America. He pioneered as the first Cal student with severe disabilities, and created the Physically Disabled Student's Program and Center for Independence Living to enable others to do the same. His actions inspired others across the nation to engage in Disability Rights, and lay paths toward the ADA (American Disability Acts).  As a Cal Alum with disability, my education and career is possible because of Roberts and others like him. 

To learn more:

values.value: I am excited to announce that the Product Design Association of Utah (PDAU) and Product Management Excellent (PMX) are joining forces to become Product Hive.
